==Korean==
===Verb===
'''갈다''' (gal-da)
# ([[耕]]) To [[till]], [[plough]], [[sow]] a crop, [[cultivate]], cf. Latin [[colere]] 
# ([[磨]]) To [[grind]], [[file]], [[polish]], [[rub]], [[whet]]
# ([[換]]) To [[change]], [[replace]]

====Derived terms====
* [[밭]]갈다 (bat-) To [[till]], [[plough]] the field 

====Related terms====
* [[고랑]] (gorang) [[furrow]] (between the two plouged ridges)  
* [[골]] (gol) [[ditch]], [[furrow]], [[groove]], [[trench]]
* [[굴]] (gul) [[cave]], [[burrow]], [[hollow]], [[tunnel]]
* [[두둑]] (dudug, duduk) raised strip of ploughed ground, [[ridge]] 
* [[밭]] (bat) (agricultural) [[bed]], [[field]], [[garden]], [[patch]]
* [[이랑]] (irang)  ploughed ground consisting of a ridge and a furrow
* [[쟁기]] (jaenggi) [[plough]]
* 쟁기[[질]] (-jil) [[plough]]ing
* 쟁기질[[하다]] (-hada) to [[plough]], [[till]]

